<exercise checkit-seed="0003" checkit-slug="LE4" checkit-title="Linear Systems with Infinitely-Many Solutions">
  <statement>
    <p>
Consider the following
vector equation.
      <me>
        
        x_{1} \left[\begin{array}{c}
5 \\
-4 \\
4 \\
-1
\end{array}\right] + x_{2} \left[\begin{array}{c}
-1 \\
1 \\
-4 \\
-2
\end{array}\right] + x_{3} \left[\begin{array}{c}
-3 \\
2 \\
4 \\
5
\end{array}\right] = \left[\begin{array}{c}
-6 \\
5 \\
-8 \\
-1
\end{array}\right]
      </me>
    </p>
    <ol>
      <li>
        <p>
Explain how to find a simpler system or vector equation
that has the same solution set.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
Explain how to describe this solution set using set notation.
        </p>
      </li>
    </ol>
  </statement>

  <answer>
    <p>
      <me>\mathrm{RREF}\left[\begin{array}{ccc|c}
5 &amp; -1 &amp; -3 &amp; -6 \\
-4 &amp; 1 &amp; 2 &amp; 5 \\
4 &amp; -4 &amp; 4 &amp; -8 \\
-1 &amp; -2 &amp; 5 &amp; -1
\end{array}\right]=\left[\begin{array}{ccc|c}
1 &amp; 0 &amp; -1 &amp; -1 \\
0 &amp; 1 &amp; -2 &amp; 1 \\
0 &amp; 0 &amp; 0 &amp; 0 \\
0 &amp; 0 &amp; 0 &amp; 0
\end{array}\right]</me>
      The solution set is <m> \left\{ \left[\begin{array}{c}
a - 1 \\
2 \, a + 1 \\
a
\end{array}\right] \,\middle|\, a \in\mathbb R \right\} </m>.
    </p>
  </answer>
</exercise>
